  <description><![CDATA[<p><span>The Crazy Reindeer Hotel is a popular choice and exce</span><span>llent value, having friendly service and a great range of rooms available. The hotel is in a quiet wooded location, around 400 metres from <a data-udi="umb://document/1b2fbafe6b3546cbbcb8a26241bb809c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/1b2fbafe6b3546cbbcb8a26241bb809c}" title="Levi">Levi</a> village centre, providing beautiful walks through this winter wonderland.</span></p>
<h2><span>Cosy lounge and relaxation</span></h2>
<p>After a day of exploring the snowy surroundings in <a data-udi="umb://document/1b2fbafe6b3546cbbcb8a26241bb809c" href="/{localLink:umb://document/1b2fbafe6b3546cbbcb8a26241bb809c}" title="Levi">Levi</a>, warm up in front of one of the log fires in the cosy and welcoming public lounge, or relax in the popular bar area with a drink. Alternatively. rejuvenate in the wellness area which features a sauna, steam room, jacuzzi and cold water plunge pool. For the ultimate treat, book a massage or beauty treatment locally, or unwind in the salt room or infrared sauna, which is available for a local fee. There is also an onsite gym so you can prepare for you next Arctic adventure. </p>
<h2>Warm and welcoming rooms </h2>
<p><span>The Crazy Reindeer offers tastefully designed, simple rooms. You can opt for a room with a sauna or a spacious family duplex that accommodates up to eight people. The rooms are situated in three neighbouring buildings, all within walking distance (around 150 metres) from the main building. Every room is equipped with the essential amenities required for a restful stay in Levi, including Wi-Fi, drying cupboards, and some even have a sauna and a balcony.</span></p>]]></description>
