  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Flying Reindeer (Superior) Twin Rooms </strong>are around 22m² and <span>sleep two to three people. These rooms have a twin beds, with the third bed being a single fold-out arm chair or roll away bed, and </span>a bath tub, shower , drying closet and a balcony.  Flying Reindeer rooms are located in the main reception building. These rooms are also available for sole occupancy.</p>
<p><span><strong>Family Duplex Rooms </strong>are around 32+12m² and sleep two to five people. These rooms have twin beds in the living area, an additional fold-out armchair bed, twin beds in the mezzanine with a sloping roof, en-suite sauna, shower, drying closet and a balcony. The rooms are located in a separate accommodation building, approximately 150 metres from the main building and reception.</span></p>
<p><strong>4-room Family Suites </strong>are around 47+30m² and sleep three to eight people. The Family Suite is made up of a double bedroom, a twin bedroom and twin beds in the mezzanine. There is also a double sofa bed in the open plan living area and kitchenette, two showers, two WC's, drying closet and sauna. The room is located in a separate building with a connecting corridor to the main building.</p>
<p>Each room must have an adult booked, children are not allowed to stay in a room without being accompanied by an adult. All rooms have twin beds which have been pushed together.</p>
<p> </p>
<p><span><strong>Bedroom facilities</strong></span></p>
<ul>
<li>En-suite with WC</li>
<li>Twin beds</li>
<li>Free Wi-Fi</li>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Fridge</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
<li>Tea and coffee making facilities</li>
</ul>]]></roomsDescription>
